n><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 9:59:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23032.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NWN</span><hr size=1> If they offered a standalone program for up to $60 that did JUST the following, I'd buy it:<br><br>1) create your own character, change any stats, skills, etc - including giving any item, xp, AAXP, etc. (or perhaps just a death touch ability with instant cast, instant recast - and you just farm your own items)<br><br>2) ability to go completely invisible - would let you inspect any zone you want, get a look at those uber encounters that you probably will never get to experience<br><br>3) GOD mode<br><br>4) few super-abilities, such as ability to repop a zone at any time, clear a zone at any time, etc.<br><br>I would actually be willing to pay up to $80 for something like this.  I never plan to join a guild that can do any high-end encounters, and this would let me see those mobs, see what they drop, and with a GOD mode, even try to kill them.  (I am sure most encounters would just never end if you engaged a GOD mode, unless you are a nuker with unlimited mana and GOD mode = automatic dodge)<br><br>How cool would it be to just walk around all the zones?  I know there are tutorial hacks that try to do this for you, but it's not the same.  Just the ability to see everything in the game would be incredible.  I know they are against something like this, because it might trivialize some of their content, but hopefully when EQ starts winding down, they do something like this.  Because even 2 years from now, I may be level 60, but I seriously doubt I will ever enter a zone like ST.  <br><br>I'm /drooling just thinking about it.  I'd love to make a level 52 rogue with all AAXP and fight Vox/Naggy for fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukelkun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelkun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 10:28:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23032.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NWN</span><hr size=1> <br>lol<br><br>Having a server would be nice, but Verant would NEVER ever do that.  Reason being is that you could play EQ without being registered to their servers.  Plus, you'd need to have the engine etc.  And patches, omg.<br><br>Once the game is done with, and no longer commercialized, releasing the source code and letting people play with it would be fun.  Imagine changing your own spells etc.<br><br>If you only want the server to cheat etc, go play Diablo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>God mode, sheesh.  I play the game for the challenge!<br><br>Kelkun<br>Proud supachanta of Arch Overseers<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugnomified.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gnomified</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 11:12:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23032.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NWN</span><hr size=1> Well, I play the game for the challenge as well.  But even thru playing my character to level 55, I have only seen about 15% of the total content.  Now that I'm high enough level, I do like to visit lower level places I never went to.  But I will NEVER be able to do that, even when I'm level 60, for pretty much any zone aimed at the 45+ crowd.  I also do not ever intend to join a guild which can do NToV, ST, etc.  A _single-player_ EQ where you could visit all these places without getting aggro would be great just to explore.  Even without letting me set my own stats, deathtouch mobs to get whatever items I want, etc., I would still buy it.  JUST to see these places and the mobs there. <br><br>I love the stories in EQ, and having a single-player mode to examine these stories would be incredible.  <br><br>I never said server.  But yes, that would be really fun too.  Get 2 friends, set them all at level 60, get equipped, and have a blast in some high-end zone getting killed.  If you honestly think that 3 level 60s with the best equipment possible can't find a challenge in the game.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>And if you're worried about being the first to be somewhere or do something, that's easily solved - don't release stuff to the single-player mode until it's been solved on the servers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urolpho.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rolpho</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/02 10:36:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23032.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dungeon Siege</span><hr size=1> www.dungeonsiege.com comes out next week <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br><br>Rolpho <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><ta